By indenture made at Stokelynche, on the 5th day of March, in the 3rd year of the reign of King Henry the Fifth; Alianor‚ widow of Walter Cloptone‚ knight‚ grants to Nicholas Yonge, clerk, Robert Veel senior, and William Kyngestone—All her lands and tenements in Stokelynche, those viz, which were delivered and assigned to her in Dowry, by the Endowment of the said Walter her late husband: on condition of the grantees paying yearly to Alianor, during her life, 44 shillings and 4 pence of legal money, at Sylveyns (her residenee) near Stokelynche.
